The '''Brokke Power Station ''' is a [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]] located in the municipality [[Valle, Norway|Valle]] in [[Aust-Agder]] county, [[Norway]]. It is located on the west shore of the river [[Otra]], about {{convert|4|km}} north of the village of [[Rysstad]]. The [[Norwegian National Road 9]] runs past the station. The facility operates at an installed capacity of {{convert|330|MW|lk=on}}. The average annual production is {{convert|1416|GWh|lk=on}}. The power station receives its water from the lake [[Botnsvatnet]] via a {{convert|30|km|adj=on}} long tunnel from the lake high up in the mountains. The water flowing down through the tunnel is used to produce the hydroelectric power.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Brokke |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Brokke|language=Norwegian|accessdate=15 August 2011}}</ref>
