{{refimprove|date=April 2012}}
The '''Zhoushan Island Overhead Powerline Tie''' is a 220 kV three-phase AC interconnection of the power grid of [[Zhoushan Island]] with that of the Chinese mainland. It runs over several islands and consists of several long distance spans, the longest with a length of {{Convert|2.7|km|mi|1}} south of Damao Island. This span uses two {{Convert|370|m|ft|adj=mid|-tall}} pylons, which are the tallest electricity pylons in the world. The north tower on Damao Island ({{zh|大猫岛}}, ''{{transl|zh|dà māo dǎo}}'') was completed in 2009, and the south tower on Liangmao Island ({{zh|凉帽岛}}, ''{{transl|zh| liángmào dǎo}}'') was completed in 2010.  These pylons resemble those of the [[Pylons of Messina|Messina Strait]], but are steel-tube lattice structures.

